{
  "texts": [
    "The first part involved the corpus translation and preparation phase, where three publicly available annotated corpora were standardized to the same format.",
    "This included translating English corpora into Dutch while preserving annotations and creating training and test sets.",
    "The second part involved applying and evaluating two concept extraction tools on the test sets, with one tool that supported supervised training, also using the training sets.",
    "The setup is visualized in Figure 1.",
    "CorporaThe annotated corpora used in our study include the MedMentions corpus (MM) [25], the corpus from the ShARe/CLEF eHealth evaluation lab task 2 (SC) [24], and the multilingual Mantra corpus (MT) [27].MM is a comprehensive biomedical corpus containing4,392 abstracts from PubMed, annotated with concepts across a wide range of biomedical fields."
  ]
}